New Records: David Willey reached 100 wickets in his last international match.
Key Match Events: David Willey took 3 wickets for 56 runs.
Haris Rauf scored 35 off 23 balls and took 3 wickets for 64 runs.
Adil Rashid took 2 wickets for 55 runs.
Haris Rauf was caught by Stokes off Woakes' bowling.
Post-Match Reflections: Jos Buttler expressed disappointment over the World Cup performance but was pleased with the win.
Buttler praised David Willey's contribution and mentioned the need for some changes in the team.
Babar Azam acknowledged the team's mistakes and emphasized the need to take wickets in the middle overs.
David Willey reflected on his career and expressed pride in his achievements.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Jos Buttler's team sealed qualification for the 2025 Champions Trophy.
The match was held at Eden Gardens, Kolkata.
David Willey was named Player of the Match in his final international match.
